NAME
lxcu-create.sh -- Create a new lxc container of a certain type.
SYNOPSIS
lxcu-create.sh [OPTIONS]
DESCRIPTION
lxcu-create.sh will create a container of a certain type for a specified
distribution, release and architecture. These types specify what extra packages
to install or cache and are specified in the sysconfdir/lxcu directory. The only
mandatory type is 'basic' so this must always be specified.
OPTIONS
-a, --arch 'arch-name' Architecture for the container

-d, --dist 'distribution-name'

-h, --help Display this help information

-n, --name 'container name'

-r, --rel 'release-name'

-t, --type 'type-name' e.g. basic or dev.....

-V, --version Print script version information
EXIT STATUS
0 - Success

1 - General failure

64 - Error in command line
FILES
lxcu.conf  The script reads the configuration file to set default values.
